Officers say the pair were handcuffed in Makhado as part of an ongoing investigation into a poaching syndicate at a game farm. JOHANNESBURG - Police have arrested two suspected rhino poachers in Limpopo.Officers say the pair were handcuffed in Makhado as part of an ongoing investigation into a poaching syndicate at a game farm in the area.One of them was wounded in a shootout with police who had been lying in wait for the group.A hunting rifle, a Ford Ranger, three hunting knives and ammunition were recovered on the scene.The police s Moatshe Ngoepe says the suspects will appear in court on Wednesday. We have intercepted a rhino poaching syndicate on a farm outside Makhado near Thohoyandou. These suspects were en route to poach rhinos, when they saw us, they started shooting and we responded. 